comment: After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the shot by DeRozan (TOR) did not touch the rim, was overturned. The officials also upheld the ruling that the ball was last touched by Denver and Toronto was awarded possession.
Carroll (TOR) and Barton (DEN) briefly engage then separate away from the ball.
Scola (TOR) does not obtain a legal guarding position prior to the body to body contact with Nelson (DEN) that affects his RSBQ.
Carroll (TOR) and Gallinari (DEN) briefly engage and separate during rebounding. The contact by Carroll is incidental.
Biyombo (TOR) sets the screen on Nelson (DEN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Biyombo (TOR) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Barton (DEN) that affects his drive to the basket and layup attempt.
Gallinari (DEN) makes contact with Lowry's (TOR) arm and body that affects his jump shot attempt.
Biyombo (TOR) and Arthur (DEN) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Denver was upheld. Toronto was awarded possession.
Nelson (DEN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Joseph's (TOR) drive.
Barton (DEN) is trapped in the corner by DeRozan (TOR), Lowry (TOR), and Carroll (TOR) who maintain legal guarding position and force the turnover.
Lowry (TOR) sets the screen on Gallinari (DEN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

RHH shows that Foye (DEN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Lowry's (TOR) drive to the basket. Lowry then initiates the contact with Arthur (DEN), who maintains legal guarding position on the shot attempt.
Carroll (TOR) commits a take foul on Foye (DEN).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Carroll's (TOR) shot attempt was a 3 point field goal was upheld.
DeRozan (TOR) commits a take foul on Barton (DEN).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Lowry's (TOR) shot attempt occurred prior to the clock expiring was upheld.
